{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "g8-analytics-collection",
    "name": "G8 Analytics Service",
    "description": "Full test suite for the G8 Analytics Service.\n\nRun in order:\n0. Security (Phase 0) — verify 401 then generate JWT token\n1. Ingest data (01-06)\n2. Wait ~60 seconds for the scheduler\n3. Read analytics (07-13) + monitoring (16-17)\n4. Generate and fetch a report (14-15)\n5. Grafana: http://localhost:3000 (admin / sgitu2026)\n\nNOTE: Request '00b - Generate JWT Token' MUST be run before any authenticated call. The token is saved automatically into {{authToken}} and applied to every subsequent request via the collection-level pre-request script.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{authToken}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "exec": [
          "// Auto-set date variables",
          "var today = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('today', today);",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('ts08', today + 'T08:00:00Z');",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('ts09', today + 'T09:00:00Z');",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('ts10', today + 'T10:00:00Z');",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('ts11', today + 'T11:00:00Z');",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('ts14', today + 'T14:00:00Z');",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('ts15', today + 'T15:30:00Z');",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('ts17', today + 'T17:00:00Z');",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('ts18', today + 'T18:00:00Z');"
        ],
        "type": "text/javascript"
      }
    }
  ],
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8088",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "authToken",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Populated automatically after running request '00b - Generate JWT Token'"
    },
    {
      "key": "reportId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Populated automatically after running request 15"
    },
    {
      "key": "today",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-set to today's date (YYYY-MM-DD) by the collection pre-request script"
    },
    {
      "key": "jwtSecret",
      "value": "sgitu_g8_secret_key_2025_very_long_secret_for_analytics",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Shared dev secret matching application.yml jwt.secret"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "--- PHASE 0: Security ---",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "00a - No Token (Expect 401 Unauthorized)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Returns 401 Unauthorized without a JWT token', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(401);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Response body contains error field', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('error');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.error).to.eql('Unauthorized');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/analytics/dashboard",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "analytics", "dashboard"]
            },
            "description": "Sends a request with NO Authorization header.\n\nExpected: 401 Unauthorized\n\nThis confirms the JWT security filter is active and rejects unauthenticated callers."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "00b - Generate JWT Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Build a HS256 JWT using the CryptoJS library bundled in Postman",
                  "var secret = pm.collectionVariables.get('jwtSecret');",
                  "",
                  "// Header",
                  "var header = { alg: 'HS256', typ: 'JWT' };",
                  "",
                  "// Payload — mirror what seed-dashboard-data.ps1 generates",
                  "var now = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);",
                  "var payload = {",
                  "    sub: 'admin',",
                  "    roles: ['ROLE_ADMIN', 'ROLE_ANALYTICS'],",
                  "    iat: now,",
                  "    exp: now + 86400  // 24 hours",
                  "};",
                  "",
                  "function base64url(str) {",
                  "    return btoa(str)",
                  "        .replace(/\\+/g, '-')",
                  "        .replace(/\\//g, '_')",
                  "        .replace(/=/g, '');",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "var encodedHeader  = base64url(JSON.stringify(header));",
                  "var encodedPayload = base64url(JSON.stringify(payload));",
                  "var signingInput   = encodedHeader + '.' + encodedPayload;",
                  "",
                  "// HMAC-SHA256 via CryptoJS",
                  "var signature = CryptoJS.HmacSHA256(signingInput, secret);",
                  "var encodedSig = CryptoJS.enc.Base64.stringify(signature)",
                  "    .replace(/\\+/g, '-')",
                  "    .replace(/\\//g, '_')",
                  "    .replace(/=/g, '');",
                  "",
                  "var token = signingInput + '.' + encodedSig;",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('authToken', token);",
                  "console.log('JWT generated and stored in {{authToken}}');"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Token was generated and stored', function () {",
                  "    var token = pm.collectionVariables.get('authToken');",
                  "    pm.expect(token).to.be.a('string').and.to.have.length.above(20);",
                  "    console.log('authToken is now: ' + token.substring(0, 40) + '...');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Dashboard responds 200 OK with valid JWT', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{authToken}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/analytics/dashboard",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "analytics", "dashboard"]
            },
            "description": "Generates a signed HS256 JWT token in the pre-request script using the shared dev secret, saves it into {{authToken}}, then immediately uses it to hit the dashboard endpoint.\n\nExpected: 200 OK (confirming the token is valid).\n\nAfter this request, ALL subsequent requests in the collection automatically carry the token via the collection-level Bearer auth."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
